Bug.WithStack:
If a class defined in global scope is refactor->renamed while a class of the
same name exists in a method, then the inner class and its references are
mistakenly renamed as well.

class Hoo{};   // A: rename Hoo from the outline view
class Foo{
	int Foot(){
		class Hoo{}; // B: Hoo should not be renamed here
		Hoo h;  // C: Hoo should not be renamed here
	}
};
This is a limitation of our index right now.  
True enough - we currently don't keep around in the index which declaration a
reference uses.
The new rename refactoring (introduced in CDT 3.0) is not based on the indexer and can correctly rename either the local or the global class.

Bug.WithOutStack:
