Bug.WithOutStack:
I have modified the code formatting defaults slightly, mostly just to columnar tabulation of arguments. In certain cases, I am getting truly bizarre formatting, for example, the code:
public class TestFormatting {
public static void main(String[] args) { try { while (true) { if (true) { if (true) { TestFormatting.longNamedMethod(true, true, "Some very long " + true + " String to break"); } } } } finally { } }
public static void longNamedMethod(boolean aBoolean, boolean anotherBoolean, String aString) { } }
reformats to this:
public class TestFormatting {
public static void main(String[] args) { try { while (true) { if (true) { if (true) { TestFormatting .longNamedMethod( true, true, "Some very long "
+ true
+ " String to break"); } } } } finally { } }
public static void longNamedMethod(boolean aBoolean, boolean anotherBoolean, String aString) {
} }
