Bug.WithStack:
I am testing refactor->rename of a global variable in a cpp file shown in the
code snippet below. An argument of the same name exists in a global function. If
I rename the "zzz" variable, refactor gets confused and renames the arguemnt too.
Expected: only zzz on lines 4 and 7 should be renamed.


class A{					
 public: int i;
};				
A zzz;           //line 4: rename zzz
void f(A zzz){	 //zzz on this line should not be renamed
  int i = zzz.i; //nor on this line
 int j = ::zzz.i; //line 7: this is correctly renamed
}
This works fine now.

